<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <% include ../partials/head %>
</head>
<body class="container">

<main>
    <h1>Berlioz Sample</h1>
    <h2>Polyglot Microservices</h2>
    <h3>Source: <a href="https://github.com/berlioz-the/sample-polyglot-microservices" target="_blank">https://github.com/berlioz-the/sample-polyglot-microservices</a></h3>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm">
            In the following sample &quot;web&quot; calls &quot;app&quot;, and &quot;app&quot; calls &quot;bill&quot;. 
            <br/>
            The &quot;web&quot; is implemented in node.js, 
            the &quot;app&quot; is implemented in python and
            the &quot;bill&quot; is implemented in Java.
            <br/>
            You can open Jaeger to see the distributed traces.
            <br/><br/>
            If you think this is not cool - you are not a real engineer!
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm">

            <div class="card <%= cardClass %>">
                <div class="card-header">
                    Response from &quot;app&quot; microservice.
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h4><%= result.message %></h4><br/>
                    Payload:
                    <pre>
<%= JSON.stringify(result.payload, null, 2) %>
                    </pre>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

    <% include ../partials/global-error %>
</main>

<footer>
    <p class="text-center text-muted">Â© Copyright 2019 Berlioz</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
